integratere(d, sd, L, k, yhat, backtrans)

integratereR(d, sd, L, k, yhat, backtrans)

Arguments

d

A list
sd

A list
L

A list
k

An integer, the number of samples
yhat

A matrix of the fixed effects predictions
backtrans

An integer, indicating the type of back transformation. 0 indicates inverse logit (e.g., for logistic regression). 1 indicates exponential (e.g., for poisson or negative binomial regression or if outcome was natural log transformed). 2 indicates square (e.g., if outcome was square root transformed).

Value

A numeric matrix with random values

  • integratereR: Pure R implementation of integratere
